originalText.text: Drove up 15 minutes before the early bird. Extremely rude guy told me to back my car out and go somewhere else down another block. Well ok then. I’ll back my car out and never come here again. I’ll also let everyone I know that lives in Sutton place to avoid this garage. Human decency goes a long way. Being kind to a customer goes a long way. Explaining a rule or regulation without being a dick goes a long way. You won’t get either at this garage. Disappointed

originalText.text: There are Two lots side by side. Today I was encountered by an individual who is on the right lot and extremely rude. I tried calling to place a complaint by speaking to a manager but I am well aware that the complaint will go nowhere. I am 38 weeks pregnant, drove up and was stopped before I reached the stop sign, was told the early bird special was over from behind his booth. I rolled my window down and said I though it's at 11 AM, he rudely directed me to the sign which is behind me at this point and I can no longer see. He rudely reiterates no its at 10 AM. I proceed to ask If the other side is at 11 AM. I had to reverse and maneuver my way to the first lot right next door which took me some time and allow another car to go ahead of me because its difficult at this point. When I was given the ticket from the other lot the time stamp showed 10:02 AM. When I went back over to let him know I didnt appreciate his tone the gentelman proceeded to yell at me and even walked away and slammed the door behind him, I  have parked at the other lot plenty of times and never experienced such service. The only reason why I attempeted to park in this lot today is because they have the debit card terminal in this lot.

originalText.text:
It's advertised on Gemini's wall that parking for 2 hours is $16.05.
Plus approximately 18% tax ( $2.89), it's $18.94. Yet they insisted I pay them $24 for just over an hour this evening. I'd say that's false advertising/theft. Park with these shifty characters and you may get ripped off. Caveat Emptor!
